The nation will finally hear from President Cyril Ramaphosa this evening. He's expected to talk about developments in the country's risk-adjusted strategy to manage the spread of COVID-19. *Editor's note: The president's address is expected to begin at 8 pm PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on Saturday evening on the strategy to manage the spread of COVID-19. READ: COVID-19 State of Disaster deadline looms The President’s address follows a meeting earlier this week of the National Coronavirus Command Council and meetings on Saturday of the President’s Coordinating Council and Cabinet. It has been five months since the coronavirus pandemic was declared a national disaster. The Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma, has extended the national state of disaster from 15 August 2020 to 15 September 2020. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.